Source: NZ Whitebait Book, The
Author: McDOWALL
Vol / Page: 152
Edition:
Quote: Whitebaiters of all types are ingenious people, and a variety of "helps" has been developed. The most common of these is the spotter board. This board is laid across the riverbed making it easier to see the shoals.
